Sentencas: Polycrystalline samples of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-delta (LCFN) with perovskite type structure have been prepared by combustion, freeze drying, citrate-gel process and liquid mix method.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The analysis of X-ray powder diffraction indicated that the samples were single phase and crystallized in an orthorhombic (space group, Pnma no. 62) structure.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) analysis on the synthesized powder at 600 degrees C by liquid mix method showed clusters of 150 nm formed by nanoparticles of 20 nm.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of LCFN cathodes, which are used for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells, were investigated.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The polarization resistance was studied using two different electrolytes: Y-doped zirconia (YSZ) and Sm-doped ceria (SDC).
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The dc four-probe measurement exhibits a total electrical conductivity, over 100 S cm(-1) at T >= 600 degrees C, pointing out that strontium can be substituted for the cheaper calcium cation without destroying the electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Experimental results indicate that nanoparticles have more advantages in terms of smaller particle size and better electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Nanoparticles of La0.8Ca0.2Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ perovskite for solid oxide fuel cell application
